excerpt: Sandy, crescent-shaped swimming beach in a rocky bay, with waterside bars & eateries.
detail_description: El Medano Beach, located just south of downtown Cabo San Lucas, is the main beach in the area and a bustling hub of activity. This crescent-shaped swimming beach is packed with visitors, locals, and vendors offering various water activities like kayaking, jet skiing, and parasailing. If you prefer a quieter atmosphere, heading to the south end or nearby Playa Chileno for snorkeling in clear waters can be a great option.
name: El Medano Beach
address: Baja California Sur, Mexico

excerpt: Cabo San Lucas, a resort city on the southern tip of Mexico’s Baja California peninsula, is known for its beaches, water-based activities and nightlife. Playa El Médano is Cabo’s main beach, with outdoor restaurants and numerous bars. Past the marina is Land's End promontory, site of Playa del Amor (Lover's Beach) and El Arco, a natural archway in the seacliffs.
detail_description: Cabo San Lucas, also known as "Cabo," is a vibrant resort city located at the southern tip of Mexico's Baja California peninsula. It offers a mix of beautiful beaches, water activities, and lively nightlife. The main beach, Playa El Médano, features outdoor dining and numerous bars. Beyond the marina lies Land's End promontory with iconic attractions like Lover's Beach and El Arco natural archway.
name: Cabo San Lucas
address: Baja California Sur, Mexico

excerpt: Bustling Marina is a hub for vacationers seeking whale-watching tours, animal encounters at the Cabo Dolphins center, kayaking excursions, and luxury boat trips. Oceanfront eateries serving ceviche and tacos sit beside lively bars on a spacious boardwalk. The high-end boutiques and casual stores of the Golden Zone shopping area draw cruise-ship crowds, and the Cultural Pavilion hosts theater and dance performances.
detail_description: Marina is a lively destination popular among vacationers looking for various activities. It offers whale-watching tours, encounters with marine life at the Cabo Dolphins center, kayaking excursions, and luxury boat trips. The area features oceanfront eateries serving local dishes and drinks, alongside vibrant bars on a spacious boardwalk. Visitors can also explore high-end boutiques and casual stores in the Golden Zone shopping area. Additionally, Marina hosts theater and dance performances at the Cultural Pavilion.
name: Marina
address: Cabo San Lucas, BCS, Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Whale Watching offers a unique experience to witness the annual migration of thousands of whales, including grays and humpbacks, from the cold Arctic waters to the warm ocean around Cabo. The season typically runs from mid-December through mid-April. Visitors have the opportunity to see whale pods with their young, as well as other marine life like dolphins, manta rays, sea lions, and whale sharks in their natural habitat.
name: Cabo Whale Watching
address: Blvd. Paseo de la Marina, Lote 7, Módulo B2, Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: El Arco, also known as The Arch, is an iconic natural rock formation in Los Cabos that serves as a gateway where the Pacific Ocean meets the Sea of Cortez. This timeless symbol becomes even more mesmerizing at sunset, creating a stunning silhouette against the colorful sky and the ocean. It's a must-see attraction for visitors looking to witness this breathtaking phenomenon in Mexico.
name: El Arco
address: Av. los Cabos, Cerro de Los Venados, 23473 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Remote Pacific beach with golden sands & dramatic limestone rock formations, accessed by boat.
detail_description: Lovers Beach is a secluded and picturesque spot located at Lands End in Los Cabos. Accessible only by boat, this remote beach offers golden sands and dramatic limestone rock formations. To reach it, visitors can arrange a glass-bottom boat ride from Medano Beach, which includes stops at iconic landmarks like the Arch at Lands End and opportunities for snorkeling and scuba diving. Once there, nestled between two prominent granite rock formations, visitors can enjoy a private paradise to relax and swim.
name: Lovers Beach
address: 23453 Cabo San Lucas, BCS, Mexico

excerpt: A well-known area landmark, this rock formation jutting out from the ocean is shaped like an arch.
detail_description: El Arco, or the Arch of Cabo San Lucas, is a stunning natural rock formation that rises majestically from the ocean, creating an iconic landmark at the meeting point of the Sea of Cortez and the Pacific Ocean. This geological wonder is part of a larger area known as Lands End (El Finisterra), where visitors can marvel at unique rock formations and often spot playful sea lions basking in the sun on nearby rocks.
name: The Arch of Cabo San Lucas
address: 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Dramatic, modern mall with fashion, restaurants, a casino & movies amid mosaic floors & waterfalls.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Cabo San Lucas, Plaza Puerto Paraiso is a modern and luxurious three-story mall that offers a wide array of shopping, dining, entertainment, and services. With over 100 stores including international brands like Adidas and Lacoste as well as traditional Mexican boutiques, it has become the social hub of the city. The mall's striking architecture features mosaic floors and cascading waterfalls, creating an inviting atmosphere for visitors to explore its offerings.
name: Plaza Puerto Paraiso
address: Lázaro Cárdenas Sn y Cabo Bello, Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Wabo Cantina, founded by rock & roll musician Sammy Hagar, is a renowned live music bar that also offers its signature Cabo Wabo Tequila. The restaurant serves a variety of late-night entrees including tacos, burritos, hot wings and burgers. Operating hours are from 9:00 AM to 12:00 AM on weekdays and from 9:00 AM to 3:00 AM on weekends.
name: Cabo Wabo Cantina
address: Vicente Guerrero S/N, Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Scenic, secluded & undeveloped stretch of sand backed by rocky cliffs, a popular sunbathing spot.
detail_description: Playa del Divorcio is a secluded and undeveloped beach with scenic views and rocky cliffs. It's accessible by water taxi from the marina or Playa Medano, dropping visitors off at Lover's Beach for a short walk to Divorce Beach. This dramatic addition to the area offers colder waters, bigger waves, and strong winds, making it unsuitable for swimming but perfect for sunbathing and exploring.
name: Playa del Divorcio
address: 23453 Cabo San Lucas, BCS, Mexico

excerpt: Colorful party spot with DJs & dancing, serving beers alongside tacos, burgers & pizzas.
detail_description: El Squid Roe is a vibrant and lively party spot in Cabo, known for its energetic atmosphere, DJs, and dancing. The venue offers a variety of food options including tacos, burgers, and pizzas to accompany the drinks served. As the night progresses in Cabo, the party mood intensifies with various clubs coming to life after 11 PM.
name: El Squid Roe - Cabo Bar & Restaurant
address: Blvd. Lázaro Cárdenas 1112, Downtown, Ildefonso Green, 23479 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: IGY Marina Cabo San Lucas is a vibrant area with plenty of attractions to explore. The Mamazzita Restaurant offers a delightful dining experience with its gourmet Mexican food menu and an ocean view. It's also a great spot for special occasions, offering packages for birthdays, anniversaries, and romantic dinners. The restaurant provides convenient amenities such as private parking and high chairs for children.
name: Marina Cabo San Lucas
address: Blvd. Paseo de la Marina, Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: If you're looking for an exhilarating yet accessible adventure in Cabo San Lucas, a hike up Mt. Solmar is a must-do! This rugged peak, located at Land's End, offers breathtaking views that make the effort worthwhile. The ascent is manageable for most ages and takes about 25-30 minutes of steady climbing on natural rock steps. While the trailhead can be tricky to locate since it’s on private property near a dog shelter, some online research will guide you there.
name: Mt. Solmar
address: 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Peninsula with sandy beaches, plus a natural arch & rocky outcrops that can be explored by kayak.
detail_description: Lands End, located at the southernmost tip of the 750-mile-long Baja California peninsula in Cabo San Lucas, is a stunning natural attraction. This half-mile headland offers sandy beaches, a natural arch, and rocky outcrops that can be explored by kayak or on nightly sunset cruises. Iconic landmarks like El Arco, Pelican Rock, Neptunes Finger, and Lovers and Divorce Beaches provide remarkable views.
name: Lands End
address: Baja California Sur, Mexico

excerpt: Cliffside golf course with sweeping ocean views offering 18 holes & a clubhouse with dining.
detail_description: Nestled along the breathtaking Pacific Coast of Cabo San Lucas, Quivira Golf Club offers an unforgettable golfing experience with its stunning cliffside location and sweeping ocean views. This 18-hole course is part of the luxurious Pueblo Bonito Sunset Beach property, where golfers can enjoy not only a challenging game but also a vibrant clubhouse featuring delightful dining options.
name: Quivira Golf Club
address: Predio Paraíso Escondido S/N, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: El Huerto Farm to Table is part of the growing farm-to-table trend in Los Cabos, located in the picturesque organic farming community of Miraflores. It's one of three acclaimed farm-to-fork eateries in Animas Bajas, offering intimate al fresco dining experiences amidst working farms. The restaurant's mission is to combine local organic ingredients to create simple, healthy, and delicious food enjoyed in a family-friendly setting.
name: El Huerto Farm to Table
address: Calle Sin Nombre SN, Rancho San Angel, 23454 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: If you're looking for a memorable evening in Cabo San Lucas, consider embarking on a sunset dinner cruise at Blvd. Paseo de la Marina 416. This experience is perfect for everyone, whether you're with friends or seeking a romantic outing. As you glide across the shimmering waters, you'll be treated to breathtaking views of the sun setting behind iconic landmarks like El Arco, painting the sky in vibrant hues of pink and orange. Indulge in delicious local cuisine while enjoying music and drinks aboard your vessel.
name: Blvd. Paseo de la Marina 416
address: Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Vibrant beachfront restaurant featuring local & global food & cocktails, plus regular live music.
detail_description: "The Office on the Beach" is a lively beachfront restaurant located on Medano Beach in Cabo San Lucas. It has been a local favorite for decades, offering a mix of local and global cuisine along with refreshing cocktails. The rustic palapa setting adds to the charm as guests enjoy dishes like tuna tiradito, Baja-style jumbo shrimp, and Baja burritos. The bar serves up margaritas made with tequila sourced by their own tequilero Jesus Nava.
name: The Office on the Beach
address: Playa El Medano S/N, El Medano Ejidal, El Medano, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Whale watching cruises & sailing tours to the Cabo San Lucas Arch, plus diving & snorkeling trips.
detail_description: Cabo Adventures is a leading tour company in Cabo San Lucas, offering a wide range of outdoor activities such as whale watching cruises, sailing tours to the Cabo San Lucas Arch, diving and snorkeling trips. The company also provides thrilling experiences like zip lining, outback camel safaris, ATV desert adventures, and swimming with whale sharks. For scuba diving enthusiasts, Cabo Adventures offers dive excursions to Land's End and Cabo Pulmo National Park.
name: Cabo Adventures
address: Boulevard Paseo de la Marina Lt 7-A, Marina, 23410 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Embark on the best adventures in Baja with Karen, an amazing guide who ensures a memorable experience. Explore Cabo Pulmo National Marine Park and witness a diverse array of marine life, from sea turtles to sea lions. With Karen's expertise, snorkeling becomes an unforgettable journey as she takes care of every detail and shares her knowledge of the area's natural history. Encounter friendly whales and their playful offspring while respecting their habitat.
name: Best Adventures in Baja Scuba Snorkeling diving tours Cabo
address: Marina del Rey Lote Muelle-c, Centro, Marina, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Pelican Rock is a popular snorkeling spot located near the iconic Arch of Cabo San Lucas. It is known for its rich marine life and decent visibility throughout much of the year. The area can get busy due to boat traffic, but it remains one of the best snorkeling locations in Los Cabos. Lovers Beach, adjacent to Pelican Rock, offers a calmer experience for those seeking relaxation.
name: Pelican Rock
address: North Pacific Ocean, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Happy Flights Cabo Parasailing offers an exhilarating experience for adventure seekers visiting Los Cabos. From December to March, visitors can witness the migration of humpback and gray whales, along with other marine life such as manta rays, sea turtles, osprey, blue-footed boobies, and sea lions like Pancho. The company provides parasailing experiences that allow participants to soar up to 500 feet above the sea for 10 minutes.
name: Happy Flights Cabo Parasailing
address: F Dock, Centro, Marina, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Baja Brewing is a must-visit destination in Cabo, offering guided brewery tours led by local experts. Visitors can learn about the brewing process, sample signature beers, and explore the brewery's history while enjoying the beautiful beer garden. The company's locations in San Jose del Cabo and Cabo San Lucas offer finely-crafted beers and pub fare in elegant settings with stunning views.
name: Baja Brewing
address: Cabo Villas Resort, Callejon del Pescador Callejón Pescadores S/N, El Medano Ejidal, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Small venue with displays related to the geological & archaeological history of Baja California Sur.
detail_description: The Museum of Natural History in Cabo San Lucas is a charming little venue that offers visitors a fascinating glimpse into the geological and archaeological heritage of Baja California Sur. Housed in what was once the region's first primary school, this museum showcases an impressive array of scientific collections, including paleontological treasures like fossils from local marine mammals, birds, and reptiles. One of its standout features is a massive whale skeleton alongside an extensive archaeology exhibition that highlights the area's rich past.
name: Museum of Natural History in Cabo San Lucas
address: Plaza Amelia Wilkes, Centro, 23410 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Breakfast dishes, Mexican snacks & drinks served on a covered terrace or at tables on the sand.
detail_description: Mango Deck is a popular spot in Cabo San Lucas known for serving breakfast dishes, Mexican snacks, and drinks on a covered terrace or at tables on the sand. It's one of the many dining options available in the area, offering a casual setting with an array of food and drink choices. While it may not be as upscale as some other nearby restaurants, Mango Deck is favored for its relaxed atmosphere and beachfront location.
name: Mango Deck
address: Playa El Medano S/N, El Medano Ejidal, El Medano, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: La Coyota is a must-visit in Cabo San Lucas, offering an extensive selection of hand-embroidered crafts, Mexican art, ceramics, and more. Housed in a converted hacienda once owned by the founder of The Office on The Beach, this multi-room shop provides high-quality and diverse items without any pressure to buy.
name: La Coyota
address: Av. Leona Vicario, Downtown, Ampliación Juárez, 23469 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Cerro de la Z is a popular spot in Cabo San Lucas, offering stunning 360-degree city views. The hike up the hill takes about 20-25 minutes at a moderate pace and is suitable for those with a moderately healthy lifestyle. It's recommended to go early for sunrise or late for sunset, and comfortable shoes are a must due to some steep parts of the trail.
name: Cerro de la Z
address: Paraíso Escondido, Paraiso Escondido, 23456 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Jet Skiing in Cabo San Lucas offers an exhilarating experience for adrenaline seekers and a fun activity for friends and family. With crystal-clear waters and a stunning coastline, jet skiing is the perfect way to explore the Sea of Cortez and its beautiful beaches. Whether you're speeding through the ocean or cooling off with water splashing around you, jet skiing provides an unforgettable adventure. The responsive customer service and accommodating crew make it a highly recommended activity in Cabo San Lucas.
name: Cabo Jet Skiing
address: El Medano Ejidal, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Roger's Glass Bottom Boat Tours in Cabo San Lucas offer a variety of boat options, including clear boats, catamarans, sailing boats, and private yachts. While some tours provide open bars and food, it's recommended to consider higher quality options for a more enjoyable experience. Departing from Cabo San Lucas Marina, these tours last a couple of hours and include refreshments.
name: Roger's Glass Bottom Boat Tours
address: El Medano Ejidal, Marina, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Sky Tours offers exhilarating aerial tours of Cabo San Lucas, providing breathtaking views of Medano Beach, Pedregal, Land's End, The Arch, and Bahia San Lucas. With a highly experienced pilot like Ernesto Magana at the helm, visitors can choose between smooth or extreme settings based on their comfort level. The tour also presents opportunities to witness marine life such as whales, dolphins, sea lions, and sea turtles from above the clear ocean waters.
name: Cabo Sky Tours
address: Cam. Viejo a San Jose, El Medano Ejidal, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Baja Anglers Fly Fishing and Light Tackle since 1996 is a renowned fishing outfit in Cabo San Lucas, known for its world-class big game sport fishing. The company offers year-round opportunities to catch a variety of fish, including amberjack, bonito, dorado, sailfish, and different types of marlin. They are especially popular among fly fishermen due to their expertise in this area. Clients have praised the professionalism of the guides and the smooth booking process.
name: Baja Anglers Fly Fishing and Light Tackle since 1996
address: Mulle L, Cabo San Lucas, Marina La, Marina, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: When visiting Cabo San Lucas, don't miss out on the opportunity to indulge in a unique tequila tasting experience at Espiritu De Agave. The hosts, Mark and Jess, are incredibly knowledgeable and provide an engaging and fun-filled session. Their private 90-minute tasting is highly recommended for a personalized exploration of artisanal tequilas such as Blanco, Reposado, and Anejo.
name: Espiritu De Agave - Cabo Tequila Tasting
address: C. Miguel Angel Herrera 10, Libertad, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Flyboard is a thrilling water activity that has gained popularity in Cabo San Lucas since its invention in 2011 by Franky Zapata, a French jet ski champion. Participants wear boots attached to a board connected to a jet ski via a hose, allowing them to soar up to 35 feet above the water's surface.
name: Cabo Flyboard
address: Av. del Pescador local 6, El Medano Ejidal, El Medano, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Golden Cactus Gallery, previously located in downtown Cabo, has recently moved to a spacious warehouse outside of town. The new location offers improved installations and ample space to showcase their collection. Visitors can schedule appointments with the owner who will personally pick them up at no extra charge. The gallery is known for its stylish ambiance and showcases the romance of Mexico through its diverse works.
name: Golden Cactus Gallery
address: Carretera a Todos Santos, Casa Blanca Km 2.5, 23473 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Dive Ninja Expeditions is a top choice for divers, especially those looking to refresh their skills after a long break from diving. The team provides excellent refresher courses and patient dive masters who guide you through easy dives, ensuring a safe and enjoyable experience. Their communication and organization are commendable, with staff reaching out before the trip to confirm details and provide necessary information. Booking through platforms like WeTravel is seamless, thanks to Dive Ninja's responsive and thoughtful team members who make the process simple.
name: Dive Ninja Expeditions
address: Ignacio Zaragoza 345 Esq, 16 de Septiembre, Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Popular beach on the main drag with bars, cafes, rentals of water sports & miles of safe swimming.
detail_description: Playa El Medano is a vibrant beach that serves as the heart of the action in the area. Stretching along the main thoroughfare, this lively spot is lined with an array of bars and cafes, making it perfect for those looking to relax or enjoy a bite to eat. For adventure seekers, there are plenty of water sports rentals available, ensuring you can dive into fun activities while enjoying miles of safe swimming.
name: Playa El Medano
address: 23473 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Expeditions offers a 75-minute tour on a yellow semi-submersible that provides stunning views of Cabo San Lucas Bay and its marine life. The climate-controlled underwater viewing cabin allows guests to spot up to 70 types of fish, including dolphins, whales, and puffer fish. Knowledgeable guides are available to answer questions about the marine life. The return trip includes close-up views of iconic rock formations like The Arch and Pelican Rock.
name: Cabo Expeditions
address: Puerto 0 Frente a Breathless Hotel El Medano, Marina de, Marina, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Easygoing beachfront destination offering drinks & snacks, as well as loungers & massages.
detail_description: The Sand Bar is a laid-back beachfront spot that offers a variety of drinks and snacks, along with amenities like loungers and massages. In Cabo San Lucas, there are numerous dining options, from cliffside restaurants with stunning views to hidden gems that transport you to another era. The diverse selection of settings and menus provides unique ambiances for every taste.
name: The Sand Bar
address: Cormoranes SN, El medano, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Guided boat tours from Dec–Apr to see humpback & gray whales, dolphins & sea turtles.
detail_description: Whale Watch Cabo is a renowned whale watching company in Los Cabos that offers guided boat tours from December to April. They are highly regarded for their conscious and eco-friendly approach, and have been TripAdvisors' top-rated whale watching company since 2011. Unlike traditional boats, Whale Watch Cabo's speedy Zodiac boat allows them to search the waters more efficiently and get closer to the whales by up to 20 meters.
name: Whale Watch Cabo
address: Plaza Bonita, Blvd. Paseo de la Marina 17, Centro, Marina, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: With a rich history of 50 years in providing tours in Mexico, Caborey has established itself as a reputable agency known for its excellence, safety, and enjoyable experiences. They are pioneers in the field of boat tours in Mexico. Situated in Cabo San Lucas, Los Cabos, their contact information can be found on their website or by calling (624) 143-8260 or emailing caborey@prodigy.net.mx.
name: Caborey
address: Blvd. Paseo de la Marina Lote 9-Local A4, Centro, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

name: Tequilera Santos Destilados Centro
address: Calle Mariano Matamoros, Centro, San Lucas, 23450 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Boisterous nightspot on the marina offering beer & cocktails, plus a dance floor & pop music DJs.
detail_description: The Nowhere Bar is a lively nightspot located on the marina in Cabo San Lucas, offering an array of beers and cocktails along with a dance floor and popular music DJs. It's renowned as one of the top dance bars in the area, providing an inviting atmosphere, affordable drinks, and a playlist featuring hits from the 80s, 90s, and 2000s. The bar boasts a modest yet charming interior with stunning views of yachts and fishing boats.
name: The Nowhere Bar
address: Blvd. Paseo de la Marina 17-Local 12-A, Centro, 23410 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

excerpt: Blue Flag golden sandy beach with showers & restrooms, popular for snorkeling, swimming & basking.
detail_description: Chileno Bay Public Beach is a popular destination for both locals and tourists in Cabo San Lucas. The beach offers golden sandy shores, clear blue waters, and calm waves, making it perfect for swimming and snorkeling. Visitors can enjoy amenities such as showers, restrooms, and vendors offering umbrellas and snacks. While the beach can get busy during midday, it remains a family-friendly spot with opportunities for relaxation and water activities.
name: Chileno Bay Public Beach
address: Baja California Sur, Mexico

name: Santa Maria Beach
address: Tourist Corridor, 23455 BCS, Mexico

detail_description: Cabo Bay is a stunning destination that offers unforgettable experiences, particularly the iconic tour to the arch, which showcases nature's beauty at its finest. Visitors can enjoy thrilling whale watching during winter months, where you might witness these magnificent creatures leaping out of the water—an awe-inspiring sight! To ensure a smooth experience and avoid any potential scams, it's advisable to book tours through reliable travel apps or directly at designated booths near each pier.
name: Cabo Bay
address: CABO BAY, BAHIA, Playa Médano, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico

detail_description: Playa Pública Cabo San Lucas, also known as Medano Beach, is a prime beachfront in Los Cabos. It's a quiet paradise with soft sand and warm waters, located less than 10 minutes' walk from the marina. The beach offers free thatched umbrellas on a first-come, first-served basis and also provides rental options.
name: Playa Pública Cabo San Lucas
address: Marina Sur, Marina, 23453 Cabo San Lucas, B.C.S., Mexico
